Problem Link:-
https://www.codingninjas.com/studio/problems/left-rotate-an-array-by-one_5026278?utm_source=striver&utm_medium=website&utm_campaign=a_zcoursetuf&leftPanelTab=1



Solution:-
public class Solution {

    static int[] rotateArray(int[] arr, int n) {
        // Write your code here.
        int temp=arr[0];

        for(int i=0;i<n-1;i++)
        {
            arr[i] = arr[i+1];
        }

        arr[n-1]=temp;

        return arr;

    }
}


T.C. -> O(N)
Space used -> O(N) -> the given array that we are using.
Extra space used is -> O(1) 
Therefore, S.C. -> O(1) , it is for the extra space used in algoritm i.e. the extra sapec that we take and use.
